data.title: Welcome to St. Cloud Technical & Community College
data.text:
Auto Body Collision Technology

You've Got Options

Diploma

With an updated degree option designed to get you in the career force more quickly, our Auto Body program gets you ready for nonstructural and structural auto repairs, as well as using your artistic capabilities with paint guns.

I always loved working on cars, and I wanted to have the mechanical abilities. I’ve got family members who are into working on fast muscle cars, and this is where I want to be.

Jon Osborn

Overlay for card in mobile

Liberal Arts & Transfer

The Ticket to Transfer

Associate of Arts

If you want to save money AND take advantage of small class sizes, SCTCC is the best place to start your bachelor's degree. Not only do we offer an AA, but you have Transfer Pathway options to customize your transfer.

I'm getting an AA, and I know classes are transferable. Plus they're much cheaper on this side. You can take an identical course for half the price and it's the same class. The small classes are outstanding: you get a lot more one-on-one.

Adric Waibel

Overlay for card in mobile

Culinary Arts

Curated Cuisine

Associate of Applied Science

Diploma

Take your passion for food to the next level with a degree from SCTCC's Culinary Arts program. With food presentation, nutrition, sanitation, and safe equipment operation, Culinary Arts will let you have fun in the kitchen for success in your career.

I took the tour of the Culinary program and met Chef Jay. He made the program sound super fun with all the things we get to do, and I thought to myself, this is it. This is the college I want to go to.

Alyssa Leopold

Overlay for card in mobile

Paramedicine

Highlighting Health Care

Associate of Applied Science

With a fast-paced career like Paramedicine, SCTCC grads get ready to save lives by training in simulations that have real-life application.

The health field seemed like a lot of fun—helping people in need. I wasn’t sure where I fit in, but then I took the EMR class in high school, and bingo. There it was.

Sainab Gaal
